      ],
      "content": "Event-Driven Architecture (EDA) is foundational to Powerhouse. Events represent meaningful changes ('Document Updated', 'Contributor Added') and trigger reactions across the system in real time. When a document is updated, different processes like validation, notifications, and analytics generation can run in parallel without blocking each other. EDA improves fault tolerance since failures in one part do not cascade due to loosely coupled design. Event histories can be replayed to debug workflows or audit past operations.",
